org.thymeleaf.templatemode

Interface ITemplateModeHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TemplateModeHandler

    public interface ITemplateModeHandler

    Common interface for all handlers of template modes.

    Any template mode can be used at the Template Engine as long as there is a handler registered for it. Template Mode Handlers define:

    • The template mode name.
    • The way templates are read and parsed in this mode: the parser (ITemplateParser).
    • The way processed template results are written (i.e. converted into output): the writer (ITemplateWriter).
    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Daniel Fernández
